The Odole-Oodua of the Source,  Kensington Adebutu, has donated a sum of N100,000,000 to the Ogun State government for the fight against the spread of coronavirus disease in the state. Adebutu, in a letter dated 31st of March, 2020, addressed to Governor Dapo Abiodun, commended the state government for its effort in combating the disease. The letter reads partly:” On behalf of myself, my entire family and organisation, we commend the concerted effort of Your Excellency to stem COVID-19 pandemic in Ogun State. “As a token of our support of your laudable initiatives, myself, family and organisation are donating a modest sum of N100,000,000 towards which, we have forwarded the necessary instruction.” YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Buy and read digital replicas of your TRIBUNE titles by subscribing through E-VENDING Nigeria’s Foreign Reserves Decline By $182.17m In 7 Days This week, Nigeria’s Foreign Exchange (FX) reserves remained under pressure, declining by $182.17 million when compared to what it was a week ago (WTD) to $35.71 billion as of March 24, 2020… Read full story PHOTOS: Lady Who Tested Positive For Coronavirus Discharged, Narrates Her Experience At Lagos Isolation Centre A lady who tested positive for coronavirus has narrated her experience inside the isolation centre in Lagos after she was discharged and was given a clean bill of health on Monday, March 30. The lady, Oluwaseun Ayodeji Osowobi, who wrote of her experience on her twitter handle, @AyodejiOsowobi, said she contracted… Read full story COVID-19: Buhari Appoints Osinbajo As Chairman, Economic Sustainability Committee President Muhammadu Buhari has set up an Economic Sustainability Committee with Vice President Yemi Osinbajo as chairman. He has also okayed financial services providers to operate during the restriction on movements and activities that he imposed on Abuja, Lagos and Ogun States to curtail the spread of coronavirus… Read full story COVID-19: Governor Makin